{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_015MXBtCydSxVPLcHsHJK9tg","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The pods are waiting for `cockroach init` to be run after all nodes are up. The issue is:\n\n1. Pod 0 is stuck at \"waiting for cockroach init\" — this means the readiness probe fails\n2. StatefulSet won't create pod 1 until pod 0 is ready (that's how StatefulSet works by default)\n\nThe fix is to make the readiness probe less strict for the initial bootstrap phase, or to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 pods start simultaneously.\n\nWith `Parallel` pod management, all 3 pods start at once, then we can run `cockroach init` to bootstrap the cluster.\nI'll update the StatefulSet to use `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all pods launch concurrently instead of waiting for each one to be ready.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":715,"cache_read_input_tokens":31908,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":715},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75691665-9529-4b1c-9b99-e26021586286","uuid":"84a9c7cc-55ff-4dae-b782-3519921f11a9","request_id":"req_011CcLU1kdWYv6MMiprbDx15"}
