{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01XVChSfTu5k2koB5cZbJ1ru","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The 3-node CockroachDB cluster is fully deployed and healthy. Here's what was created:\n\n**Resources deployed:**\n- `Service/crdb-cluster` — headless service (ClusterIP: None) for pod DNS, exposing grpc/26257 and http/8080\n- `Service/crdb-cluster-public` — standard ClusterIP service for SQL/admin access\n- `StatefulSet/crdb-cluster` — 3 replicas, `podManagementPolicy: Parallel`, image `cockroachdb/cockroach:v23.2.0`, each advertising its pod DNS (e.g. `crdb-cluster-0.crdb-cluster.cockroachdb.svc.cluster.local`)\n- `PodDisruptionBudget/crdb-cluster-pdb` — `minAvailable: 2`, ensuring at most 1 voluntary disruption at a time (quorum preserved)\n- 3 PVCs bound at 10Gi each\n\n**Key detail:** The StatefulSet uses `podManagementPolicy: Parallel` so all 3 pods start simultaneously (required since each node waits for peers before accepting `cockroach init`). After all pods reached Running state, `cockroach init` was run once to bootstrap the cluster. All 3 nodes report `is_available=true, is_live=true`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1147,"cache_read_input_tokens":35606,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1147},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"75691665-9529-4b1c-9b99-e26021586286","uuid":"b2c8cc79-84b4-4e70-a28a-423338da4322","request_id":"req_011CcLUEnEcJQmD6y2J7Ncg7"}
